<paper id="1485733778"><title>Automatic Determination of Communication Topologies in Mobile Systems</title><year>1998</year><authors><author org="LIX, Ecole Polytechnique" id="2805835881">Arnaud Venet</author></authors><n_citation>35</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>383327177</reference><reference>1479857408</reference><reference>1503973138</reference><reference>1505745216</reference><reference>1507802114</reference><reference>1537016031</reference><reference>1537510808</reference><reference>1563480347</reference><reference>1579974221</reference><reference>1599545360</reference><reference>1726736548</reference><reference>1975791434</reference><reference>1983820815</reference><reference>2013672985</reference><reference>2025554746</reference><reference>2031373197</reference><reference>2036601332</reference><reference>2043100293</reference><reference>2055378322</reference><reference>2084875723</reference><reference>2110425399</reference><reference>2128932399</reference><reference>2132661148</reference><reference>2135697103</reference></references><venue id="1137552346" type="C">Static Analysis Symposium</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-49727-7_9</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.59928">Mobile computing</keyword><keyword weight="0.5136">Intelligent agent</keyword><keyword weight="0.48505">Formal language</keyword><keyword weight="0.46312">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.53918">Abstract interpretation</keyword><keyword weight="0.49205">π-calculus</keyword><keyword weight="0.48639">Network topology</keyword><keyword weight="0.47616">Program analysis</keyword><keyword weight="0.48261">Semantics</keyword><keyword weight="0.47344">Distributed computing</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>The interconnection structure of mobile systems is very difficult to predict, since communication between component agents may carry information which dynamically changes that structure. In this paper we design an automatic analysis for statically determining all potential links between the agents of a mobile system specified in the π-calculus. For this purpose, we use a nonstandard semantics of the π-calculus which allows us to describe precisely the linkage of agents. The analysis algorithm is then derived by abstract interpretation of this semantics.</abstract></paper>